         <abstract id="aspace_095f051c7c9ed5c7d504a6e45c4f79d6">Correspondence and William Priest's medical day book detailing medical services provided to patients (1807-1810) and the fees charged. The letters also relate to medicine: one from a doctor describing his diagnosis and prescription for a patient with liver trouble and another concerning the uses of a variety of medicines.</abstract>
